00:03:16.800 --> 00:03:18.800
So now we've looked at
skating in the straight line,

00:03:18.900 --> 00:03:20.900
it´s time to start thinking
about the corners.

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:25.900
When looking at corners, 
the easiest way to turn the corner is to use your body.

00:03:25.900 --> 00:03:28.200
Think your body like a steering wheel in
a car.

00:03:28.200 --> 00:03:32.100
When you want to go left,
you turn left with your body like this.

00:03:32.100 --> 00:03:35.600
When you want to go right,
you turn right with your body like this.

00:03:35.600 --> 00:03:39.500
When practicing this exercise,
start on a bigger radius corner

00:03:39.500 --> 00:03:42.200
and as you get more confident
and more advanced,

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:45.000
slowly make the corner
tighter and tighter.

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:48.300
It´s also important that you
practice turning left and right.

00:03:48.300 --> 00:03:52.000
The way we do this, is lay some cones or
other objects on the ground

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:55.800
and then slalom your body through them
using your body weight to turn,

00:03:55.800 --> 00:03:58.000
both left and right.

00:04:00.300 --> 00:04:01.600
The world is not flat.

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:05.300
So therefore it´s also important to practice
jumping obstacles and things.

00:04:05.300 --> 00:04:08.600
At first, start just practicing
without an obstacle.

00:04:08.600 --> 00:04:13.700
Then step by step, practice jumping.
It´s important you always keep your feet

00:04:13.700 --> 00:04:18.800
under your body, so therefore you have
complete balance. exactly like that.

00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:21.500
Now that we´ve been through many of the basic exercises,

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:24.800
it´s important that we maybe start
looking at something more advanced.

00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:28.700
the most simple advanced exercise
is skating backwards.

00:04:28.700 --> 00:04:33.500
To skate backwards first we need to turn.
A simple 180 like so...

00:04:33.500 --> 00:04:34.900
Turning the body first,

00:04:34.900 --> 00:04:38.900
and then the hips and
the rest of the body will follow.

00:04:38.900 --> 00:04:42.600
Thank you for watching this Powerslide tutorial!
We hope you learned something

00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:45.500
and you can take it and
make skating more fun!

